                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="14097842" author="apurtell" created="Thu, 14 Aug 2014 22:44:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We want the availability check to quickly and accurately determine if HBase is reachable and up. Seems like that is working as intended according to the description above. The default retry count meant to allow the client to ride over a blip in connectivity wouldn&apos;t necessarily be what is desired for a service availability check. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14098287" author="anoop.hbase" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2014 07:25:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agree with Andy here.  In your app, if you want the retry for the availability check, can consider doing retry at the app level?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14098423" author="orenrazon" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2014 10:27:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I understand your perspective but I think that if I set HBase retry to X (which is &amp;gt;1) so as a user whenever I approach HBase my intent is that and sudden blip connectivity issue won&apos;t cause me to any problem at the application level.&lt;br/&gt;
However in the state I was dealing with I had to dive into HBase code to understand that for that specific case the configuration is hard coded to &quot;1&quot; and therefor I should implement such retry on the application level.&lt;br/&gt;
I believe current state is not a big issue cause as a user I can do retry in the application level but I think it&apos;s a bit misleading and for my case caused me to several hours of work to understand why it work with only 1 retry &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14098875" author="apurtell" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2014 18:19:35 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I believe current state is not a big issue cause as a user I can do retry in the application level but I think it&apos;s a bit misleading and for my case caused me to several hours of work to understand why it work with only 1 retry&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Makes sense. I&apos;ve updated this issue as a documentation improvement. Please let us know if you disagree with this approach.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14098883" author="orenrazon" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2014 18:25:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Andrew! Make sense to me &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
